  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The plateau is not a fitness ceiling—it's a **convergence trap**. After 650 cycles, successful morphotypes have been discovered and refined to local optima. The system explores less because winners dominate. The fitness function itself (beauty + survival + efficiency) has reached its equilibrium under the fixed rule set. Structural change must either expand the rule set (new cell types, new world dynamics) or rewire selection pressure to **reward the precursors of diversity** rather than just the winners. Parameter tuning cannot break this because the landscape itself is static.; [medium] Introduce specialized cell types: sensory, resonator, and communicator cells alongside current morphology. Sensory cells detect local gradients. Resonator cells produce harmonic oscillations (new beauty dimension). Communicator cells exchange state with neighbors, enabling collective behavior. — Current morphospace (boundary, storage, motor) is fully explored. New cell types expand the design space by 3+ orders of magnitude. Collective behavior breaks single-organism optimization and creates new selective pressures. Harmonic resonance adds beauty dimension that rewards complex internal coordination rather than just external shape.; [hard] Make world chemistry co-evolve: nutrient distribution responds to ecosystem composition. If ecosystem is dominated by one morphotype, nutrient clustering becomes inverted. When diversity increases, resources become more evenly distributed. Add slow geological drift that reorganizes resource clusters every N cycles. — Fixed world is a fixed fitness landscape—organisms converge to exploit it. Dynamic world creates moving targets and arms races. An organism that exploits monoculture conditions triggers the world to punish monoculture, forcing ongoing adaptation. This creates open-ended evolution where no strategy ever dominates forever.; [easy] Decouple individual fitness from population beauty score. Add a new selection criterion: organisms that produce offspring with HIGHER behavioral variance (controlled randomness in motor decisions) get selection bonus, even if that variance reduces immediate survival. Reward exploratory genomes, not just winners. — Current selection freezes on local optima because success = convergence. By rewarding the genetic precursors to diversity (behavioral volatility), evolution avoids premature convergence. Plateau occurs when population has converged; forcing genetic explorers to survive breaks lock-in. Pairs with resonator cells to evolve coordinated group movement exploration.",
